Our product has several custom views, when using the pessimistic filesystem 
provider we encounter problems that stop our views from working. The problem 
appears to be in the getProvider method below. Adding a guard against a null
project resolves this issue.

private PessimisticFilesystemProvider getProvider(IResource resource) {
	// Guard against a null project
	IProject project= resource.getProject();
	if (project == null) return null;

	return (PessimisticFilesystemProvider)
		RepositoryProvider.getProvider(project,
		PessimisticFilesystemProviderPlugin.NATURE_ID);
}
